[ctns_make id='axClosureQ1-1']

    [ctns_question style='width:70%;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;']
The set of natural numbers is closed under addition.
    [/ctns_question]
    
    [ctns_right style='width:70%;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;']
The sum $$a+b$$ is itself a natural number for any two natural numbers $$a$$ and $$b$$.
    [/ctns_right]

    [ctns_wrong style='width:70%;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;']
The question asks whether the sum of any two natural numbers is itself a natural number. To understand what this question is asking, try adding together pairs of natural numbers to see whether you can find a pair of numbers whose sum is not a natural number.
    [/ctns_wrong]
    
    [ctns_undecided style='width:70%;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;']
The question asks whether the sum of any two natural numbers is itself a natural number. To understand what this question is asking, try adding together pairs of natural numbers to see whether you can find a pair of numbers whose sum is not a natural number.
    [/ctns_undecided]
    
[/ctns_make]
